From a post on Eclipse Corner (Paul T. Keyser, 4-FEB-2002, 10:28 AM EST)
Title: "UniversalUniqueIdentifier"?


Linux (RedHat 6.2), Eclipse R1.0 (build 137) 

Several times, but only intermittently, I have had a project open (at least 
once, directly after freshly starting eclipse), tried to save a modified 
java-file, and eclipse refuses ("Save failed: null"); when I try a second (or 
third or ...) time, the error changes to "Save failed: 
org/eclipse/core/internal/utils/UniversalUniqueIdentifier" -- what is that and 
why is it happening and how do I fix it? 

In at least one case, I have not yet been able to save the file (in other cases, 
restarting eclipse or even rebooting linux allowed eclipse to get its act 
together).

PS -- seems to be a workspace-level problem, as it afflicts every project I've 
tried; plus when I close Eclipse, I get the highly-descriptive error-messages: 

   Problems saving workspace
   Reason:
   Problems occurred while trying to save the state of the workbench.

on the linux-console.  The logfile ".log" in the .metadata directory is 
attached.
